<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,151,428]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,295,320]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Discussion.</emphasis>
This robust species was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[801,969,295,319]" name="French Guiana" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
in South 
<collectingCountry box="[1083,1179,295,319]" name="United States of America" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">America</collectingCountry>
and these are the first records from 
<collectingCountry box="[303,391,332,356]" name="Panama" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Panamá</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[446,565,332,356]" name="Venezuela" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
. The variegated elytra and weakly red head almost take it out of the fly mimicry syndrome. Two males each measure 
<quantity box="[615,715,367,391]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="4.8">4.80 mm</quantity>
long, females measure 5.00– 
<quantity box="[1044,1144,367,391]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="5.8">5.80 mm</quantity>
long (mean = 
<quantity box="[1308,1410,367,391]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.47" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="5.47">5.47 mm</quantity>
, n = 
<number box="[173,190,404,428]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="4.0">4</number>
).
</paragraph>
